From Andreas Helke Subject Re Please help an Amiga user find comfort in Windows In article Steve Lombardi writes From Steve Lombardi Subject Please help an Amiga user find comfort in Windows Date May GMT By night I'm an Amiga By day I work with I'd be much more comfortable in windows if I had Two A good Personal information You know a calendar address book reminder list rolled into one clean A good file Microsofts is very poor by my How about one that has a left and right window and allows file operations between being able to launch programs from the same interface would be as well as text reading and graphics Those who are familiar with Directory Opus on the Amiga know what I'm looking I have written the file manager HFM wich has two windows which compare the files in two directorys to find out wether there are equal or similar The most important operations copy move delete show the file start a progam navigate in the directory tree can be invoked by dragging a directory entry with the This is very convenient because the selection of the file and the operation to be performed occur in one For bitmap graphic viewing the program vpic can be integrated for spreadsheat and database files I use the view program from PCTOOLS HFM can be configured to use arbitrary viewers to show special data It does also present archives from pkzip as simulated This filemanager has a somewhat non standart user interface but it is very convienient to use and is the prefered file manager in several labs in our The drawback of this filemanager is it's still a dos program and the development of a windows version has not yet I use the program package where run tells its windows companion which windows program should be In this way you can start a windows program from a The new version to be released soon includes a new command for automating this windows program FTP archives for the mentioned programs all these archives have several mirror sites Simtel filutl gif Garbo dirutil CICA util Andreas Helke Molekulare Genetik Universitaet Heidelberg Germany email The header of this posting does not contain a valid smtp mail